reviewText: Love the history, look how the government added the cute little music to the films.
Love these great old films! Minus the misunderstanding they had about forest fire management, the information is actually still quite relevant today.
Quality is less than sub par.
Was hoping to see a more man cutting trees and actual moving them in depth.

I bought this for my husband who loves the woods and has a great interest in logging and its history.  He absolutely loves it.  It has some great stories and some old forestry commercials one is from 1920, no sound just subtitles. Seeing the old equipment and methods is very interesting.
Disappointing, I  expected more details and information. It was more of a story about  a forest ranger and his daily routine.
well done and gives a good insight what the old loggers experienced. There should be a follow up showing modern day logging.
